Computational analyses used on Disrupting the ArcA regulatory network increases tetracycline susceptibility of TetR Escherichia coli manuscript

Mario Arrieta-Ortiz et al.

October 6, 2020

  1. Load required libraries
library(corpcor)
library(gdata)
library(ggplot2)
library(gplots)
library(growthcurver)
library(igraph)

1.1 Load gene annotation related to efflux pumps, metabolism and transcriptional regulation

#load transcriptional regulatory network compiled from RegulonDB (http://regulondb.ccg.unam.mx)
load("../Data/Miscellaneous_files/Ecoli_TRN.RData")
#transcription factor (TF) names
tf.names<-colnames(transcriptional.network)
tf.names<-sapply(1:length(tf.names),function(x){strsplit(tf.names[x],split="_")[[1]][2]})
#read list of metabolic genes on the E. coli metabolic model iJO1366 (Orth et al. 2011, MSB)
metabolic.genes<-read.csv("../Data/Miscellaneous_files/genes_metabolic_model_iJO1366.csv")
metabolic.genes<-metabolic.genes$Model.genes
#read efflux pump related genes
effluxPump.genes<-read.csv("../Data/Miscellaneous_files/efflux_pump_genes.csv",header=T)
effluxPump.genes<-effluxPump.genes$Locus
#exclude TFs and efflux pump related genes from the metabolic category
metabolic.genes<-setdiff(metabolic.genes,union(tf.names,effluxPump.genes))
#function to convert locus tag to standard gene name (e.g., b0001 to thrL)  
ecoli.trn.genes<-rownames(transcriptional.network)
convert.gene.name<-function(geneList)
{
  output<-sapply(1:length(geneList),function(x){strsplit(ecoli.trn.genes[grep(geneList[x],ecoli.trn.genes)],split="_")[[1]][1]})
  output
}

1.2 Differential expression analysis of transcriptional data reported by Handel et al (2014)

#perform differential expression analysis with bayesian T-test using Cyber-T (Baldi and Long, 2001)
#code downloaded from http://cybert.ics.uci.edu
source("Bayesian_Ttest/cyberTtest.R")
#read normalized GEO data (GSE57084)
handel.normalized.matrix<-read.csv("../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/GEO_Handel2014/Handel_normalized_GEO_data.csv",header=T,row.names = 1)
#read map between microarray probe IDs and locus tags
probes.loci.map<-read.csv("../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/GEO_Handel2014/probes_loci_array_map.csv",header = T,row.names=1)
probes.loci.map<-as.matrix(probes.loci.map)
#change probe names in expression matrix with locus tags
rownames(handel.normalized.matrix)<-probes.loci.map[rownames(handel.normalized.matrix),"ORF"]
#run the differential expression analyses 
#WT(+TET) vs WT(-TET) - WT response to tetracycline
wt.response<-bayesT(handel.normalized.matrix[,1:6],numC = 3,numE = 3,conf = 7,doMulttest = T)
#define list of differentially expressed genes (DEGs)
wt.response.degs<-rownames(wt.response)[which(wt.response$BH < 0.05 & abs(wt.response$meanC - wt.response$meanE)>1)]
print(paste("WT differentially expressed",length(wt.response.degs),"genes in response to tetracycline",sep=" "))
[1] "WT differentially expressed 93 genes in response to tetracycline"
#create vector with fold-change for all genes
wt.response.fold.change<-wt.response$meanE - wt.response$meanC
names(wt.response.fold.change)<-rownames(wt.response)
#independent count of up- and down-regulated genes
wt.deg.up<-wt.response.degs[which(wt.response.fold.change[wt.response.degs]>0)]
wt.deg.down<-wt.response.degs[which(wt.response.fold.change[wt.response.degs]<0)]
#save up- and down-regulated genes in .csv files for downstream analysis on DAVID
write.csv(file="../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/DAVID_enrichment_analysis/Input/wt_response_up.csv",wt.deg.up,row.names = F)
write.csv(file="../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/DAVID_enrichment_analysis/Input/wt_response_down.csv",wt.deg.down,row.names = F)
#count TF, efflux pump  and metabolic genes in each group of DEGs
#print names of up-regulated TFs
up.tfs<-length(which(wt.deg.up %in% tf.names))
convert.gene.name(wt.deg.up[which(wt.deg.up %in% tf.names)])
[1] "relB" "nac"  "rpoS" "gadE" "gadW" "gadX" "glnG"
#print names of up-regulated efflux pump genes (eps)
up.eps<-length(which(wt.deg.up %in% effluxPump.genes))
convert.gene.name(wt.deg.up[which(wt.deg.up %in% effluxPump.genes)])
[1] "mdtE" "mdtF"
#up-regulated metabolic genes
up.metabolic<-length(which(wt.deg.up %in% metabolic.genes))
#other up-regulated genes
up.others<-length(wt.deg.up)-(up.tfs+up.eps+up.metabolic)
#compile values in a single vector
up.wt.vector<-cbind(up.others,up.metabolic,up.tfs,up.eps)
#repeat the analysis for the down-regulated genes
#print names of down-regulated TFs
down.tfs<- -1*length(which(wt.deg.down %in% tf.names))
convert.gene.name(wt.deg.down[which(wt.deg.down %in% tf.names)])
[1] "stpA"
#no down-regulated efflux pump genes (eps)
down.eps<- -1*length(which(wt.deg.down %in% effluxPump.genes))
#down-regulated metabolic genes
down.metabolic<- -1*length(which(wt.deg.down %in% metabolic.genes))
#other down-regulated genes
down.others<- -1*length(wt.deg.down)-(down.tfs+down.eps+down.metabolic)
#compile values in a single vector
down.wt.vector<-cbind(down.others,down.metabolic,down.tfs,down.eps)
#differential expression analysis for TetR(-TET) vs WT(-TET)-baseline change
tetR.basal<-bayesT(handel.normalized.matrix[,c(1:3,7:9)],numC = 3,numE = 3,conf = 7,doMulttest = T)
tetR.basal.degs<-rownames(tetR.basal)[which(tetR.basal$BH < 0.05 & abs(tetR.basal$meanC - tetR.basal$meanE)>1)]
print(paste("TetR (-TET) differentially expressed",length(tetR.basal.degs),"genes with respect to WT(-TET)",sep=" "))
[1] "TetR (-TET) differentially expressed 197 genes with respect to WT(-TET)"
#save fold-change for all genes
tetR.basal.fold.change<-tetR.basal$meanE - tetR.basal$meanC
names(tetR.basal.fold.change)<-rownames(tetR.basal)
#independent count of up- and down-regulated genes
tetR.basal.degs.up<-tetR.basal.degs[which(tetR.basal.fold.change[tetR.basal.degs]>0)]
tetR.basal.degs.down<-tetR.basal.degs[which(tetR.basal.fold.change[tetR.basal.degs]<0)]
#save up- and down-regulated genes in .csv files for downstream analysis on DAVID 
write.csv(file="../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/DAVID_enrichment_analysis/Input/tetR_basal_up.csv",tetR.basal.degs.up,row.names = F)
write.csv(file="../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/DAVID_enrichment_analysis/Input/tetR_basal_down.csv",tetR.basal.degs.down,row.names = F)
#count TF, efflux pump and metabolic genes in each group
#print names of up-regulated TFs
up.tfs<-length(which(tetR.basal.degs.up %in% tf.names))
convert.gene.name(tetR.basal.degs.up[which(tetR.basal.degs.up %in% tf.names)])

#up-regulated metabolic genes

#other up-regulated genes

1.3 Fig. S1 and Fig. S2

#Fig. S1 (relative transcript level changes of fermentation-related genes)
fermentation.ecocyc<-read.csv("../Data/Miscellaneous_files/fermentation_pathway_ecocyc.csv",header=F)
#convert gene names to locus tags
fermentation.loci<-c()
for(g in fermentation.ecocyc[,1])
{
  gene.pos<-grep(g,rownames(transcriptional.network))
  if(length(gene.pos)>0)
  {
    fermentation.loci<-c(fermentation.loci,strsplit(rownames(transcriptional.network)[gene.pos],split="_")[[1]][2])
  }
  else
  {
    fermentation.loci<-c(fermentation.loci,g)
  }
}
#add missing loci
fermentation.loci[15:16]<-c("b1675","b2929")
#create matrix with average expression value for WT and TetR strains in the presence/absence of tetracycline
handel.average.expression<-cbind(rowMeans(handel.normalized.matrix[,1:3]),rowMeans(handel.normalized.matrix[,4:6]),rowMeans(handel.normalized.matrix[,7:9]),rowMeans(handel.normalized.matrix[,10:12]))
fermentation.pathway.expression.matrix<-handel.average.expression[as.vector(fermentation.loci),]
rownames(fermentation.pathway.expression.matrix)<-as.vector(fermentation.ecocyc$V1)
colnames(fermentation.pathway.expression.matrix)<-c("WT(-TET)","WT(+TET)", "TetR(-TET)", "TetR(+TET)")
#heatmap fold-change breaks
my.breaks<-c(-3,-2,-1,-0.5,0,0.5,1,2)
#heatmap color palette
my.colors<-colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(7, "RdBu")) )(8)[8:1]
pheatmap(fermentation.pathway.expression.matrix[,2:4]-fermentation.pathway.expression.matrix[,1],scale="none",color =my.colors[-5],cluster_rows=F,cluster_cols = F,fontsize = 12,angle_col = 90,
         breaks = my.breaks,legend_breaks=c(-3,-2,-1,-0.5,0,0.5,1,2),legend=T, main="Fig. S1")
#Evaluate significance of fold-change using random permutation
#Total permutations
N=10000
#average fold change for fermentation genes in the baseline change in TetR
true.average.fold.change.fermetation<-mean(fermentation.pathway.expression.matrix[,3]-fermentation.pathway.expression.matrix[,1])
random.compilation<-c()
for(n in 1:N)
{
  random.fold.change.fermentation<-tetR.basal.fold.change[sample(1:length(tetR.basal.fold.change),33)]
  random.compilation<-c(random.compilation,mean(random.fold.change.fermentation))
}
#permutation p-value
permutation.pval<-length(which(abs(random.compilation) >= abs(true.average.fold.change.fermetation)))/N
print(permutation.pval)
[1] 0.0066

 acrA<-"b0463"
 acrB<-"b0462"

 par(mfrow=c(2,2))

 boxplot(ylim=c(-0.1,1.5),efflux.pumps.expression.matrix,col=rep("white",3),outline=T,boxlty=1,whisklty = 1, staplelty = 1, names=c("WT(+TET)","TetR(-TET)","TetR(+TET)"),frame=F,ylab="Average log2 fold-change",cex.lab=1.1,main="Fig. S2A")
dots.shapes<-c(2,1,0)
dots.colors<-c("green","orange","purple")
for(r in 1:3)
 {
   points(y=efflux.pumps.expression.matrix[r,],x=1:3,pch=dots.shapes[r],col=dots.colors[r])
}
legend("bottomright",inset=0.03,box.lty=0.1,box.lwd=0.2,
       c("AcrA","AcrB","AcrZ"),col=dots.colors,cex=0.65,pch=dots.shapes)
#Fig. S2B
#load fitness data from Nichols et al. (Cell 2011)
fitness.scores<-read.xls("../Data/Miscellaneous_files/phenotipic landscape table s2.xls",header=T,fill=T)
boxplot(ylim=c(-12,2),t(fitness.scores[c(3965,1278,2819),313:316]),col=dots.colors,outline=T,boxlty=1,whisklty = 1, staplelty = 1, names=c("acrA","acrB","acrZ"),frame=F,ylab="Deletion fitness score",cex.lab=1.1,main="")
abline(h=0,lty=2)

1.4 Fig. 1B and Table S1

#differential expression analysis for TetR(+TET) vs WT(-TET)
tetRplus.WTminus<-bayesT(handel.normalized.matrix[,c(1:3,10:12)],numC = 3,numE = 3,conf = 7,doMulttest = T)
#differentially expressed genes (DEGs)
tetRplus.WTminus.degs<-rownames(tetRplus.WTminus)[which(tetRplus.WTminus$BH < 0.05 & abs(tetRplus.WTminus$meanC - tetRplus.WTminus$meanE)>1)]
print(paste("TetR(+TET) differentially expressed",length(tetRplus.WTminus.degs),"genes with respect to WT(-TET)",sep=" "))
[1] "TetR(+TET) differentially expressed 932 genes with respect to WT(-TET)"
#save fold-change for all genes
tetRplus.WTminus.fold.change<-tetRplus.WTminus$meanE - tetRplus.WTminus$meanC
names(tetRplus.WTminus.fold.change)<-rownames(tetRplus.WTminus)
#independent count up- and down-regulated genes
tetRplus.WTminus.degs.up<-tetRplus.WTminus.degs[which(tetRplus.WTminus.fold.change[tetRplus.WTminus.degs]>0)]
tetRplus.WTminus.degs.down<-tetRplus.WTminus.degs[which(tetRplus.WTminus.fold.change[tetRplus.WTminus.degs]<0)]
#save up- and down-regulated genes in .csv files for downstream DAVID analysis
write.csv(file="../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/DAVID_enrichment_analysis/Input/tetR+TET_WT-TET_upregulated.csv",tetRplus.WTminus.degs.up,row.names = F)
write.csv(file="../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/DAVID_enrichment_analysis/Input/tetR+TET_WT-TET_downregulated.csv",tetRplus.WTminus.degs.down,row.names = F)
# Fig. 1B -heatmap with selected functional terms
#choose color scheme
colors <- colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(3, "YlGnBu")) )(3)
#read DAVID output (i.e. functional enrichment) for WT response
#terms associated with down-regulated genes
david.wt.response.down<-read.csv("../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/DAVID_enrichment_analysis/Output/david_wt_response_down.csv",header=T)
position.wt.response.down<-which(david.wt.response.down$Benjamini < 0.05)
significant.terms.wt.response.down<-as.character(david.wt.response.down$Term[position.wt.response.down])
#vector with all enriched terms
all.enriched.terms<-significant.terms.wt.response.down
#terms associated with up-regulated genes
david.wt.response.up<-read.csv("../Data/Differential_expression_analysis/DAVID_enrichment_analysis/Output/david_wt_response_up.csv",header=T)
position.terms.wt.response.up<-which(david.wt.response.up$Benjamini < 0.05)
significant.terms.wt.response.up<-as.character(david.wt.response.up$Term[position.terms.wt.response.up])
all.enriched.terms<-union(all.enriched.terms,significant.terms.wt.response.up)

#Function that creates input files for NetSurgeon
create.netSurgeon.input<-function(input.network,bayesian.ttest.output,output.file)
{
#change gene names to locus tags
rownames(input.network)<-sapply(1:nrow(input.network),function(x){strsplit(rownames(input.network)[x],split="_")[[1]][2]})
colnames(input.network)<-sapply(1:ncol(input.network),function(x){strsplit(colnames(input.network)[x],split="_")[[1]][2]})
#focus on genes present in both datasets (i.e., expression matrix and transcriptional network)
genes.present.in.both.datasets<-intersect(rownames(bayesian.ttest.output),rownames(input.network))
#filter the TRN network accordingly
input.network<-input.network[genes.present.in.both.datasets,]
#remove TFs with less than five targets 
tfs.to.be.deleted<-which(colSums(abs(input.network))<5)
input.network<-input.network[,-1*tfs.to.be.deleted]
#NetSurgeon input network is TFs x Genes
write.table(t(input.network),col.names=F,row.names=F,quote=F,file=paste("../Data/Network_analysis/NetSurgeon/Input/",output.file,".mtr",sep=""))
#extract q-values from Bayesian T-tests
q.values<-bayesian.ttest.output[rownames(input.network),"BH"]
#replace zeroes with minimum q-value among the non-zero ones to avoid infinity values in the log conversion
zero.q.values<-which(q.values ==0)
if(length(zero.q.values)>0)
{
  q.values[zero.q.values]<-min(q.values[-1* zero.q.values])
}
#convert q-values of non-differentially expressed genes to 1
q.values[which(q.values > 0.05 | abs(bayesian.ttest.output[rownames(input.network),"meanC"]-bayesian.ttest.output[rownames(input.network),"meanE"])<1)]=1
#estimate the sign of fold-change for each gene
fc.sign<- sign(bayesian.ttest.output[rownames(input.network), "fold"])
#sign -log q-values based on fold change direction
DEvector<- fc.sign * -log2(q.values) 
#remove any NA
DEvector[which(is.na(DEvector))]<-0
#save file
write.table(DEvector,sep=" ",col.names=F,row.names=F,quote=F,file=paste("../Data/Network_analysis/NetSurgeon/Input/",output.file,".vect",sep=""))
regulators<-colnames(input.network)
write.table(regulators,sep=" ",col.names=F,row.names=F,quote=F,file=paste("../Data/Network_analysis/NetSurgeon/Input/",output.file,".tfs",sep=""))
targets<-rownames(input.network)
write.table(targets,sep=" ",col.names=F,row.names=F,quote=F,file=paste("../Data/Network_analysis/NetSurgeon/Input/",output.file,".orfs",sep=""))
}
#Create files for WT response to tetracycline
create.netSurgeon.input(input.network = transcriptional.network,bayesian.ttest.output = wt.response,output.file = "WT_TET")
#Create files for TetR at baseline
create.netSurgeon.input(input.network = transcriptional.network,bayesian.ttest.output = tetR.basal,output.file = "TetR_basal")
#Create files for TetR response to tetracycline
create.netSurgeon.input(input.network = transcriptional.network,bayesian.ttest.output = tetR.response,output.file = "TetR_response")

  egrin2.genes<-union(egrin2.genes,current.corem)
}
names(ecoli.corems)<-paste("c",1:length(ecoli.corems),sep="")
#Function to identify corems enriched with a particular (specified by the user) set of genes
evaluate.corem.enrichment<-function(corem.set,gene.set)
{
  #matrix with p-values
  corem.enrichment = matrix(nrow=length(corem.set),ncol=5)
  colnames(corem.enrichment)<-c('q','m','n','k','p_value')
  rownames(corem.enrichment)<-names(corem.set)
  for(x in 1:length(corem.set)) {
    q = length(intersect(corem.set[[x]],gene.set))
    m = length(corem.set[[x]])
    k = length(intersect(gene.set,unique(egrin2.genes)))
    n = 1572-m
    pv = NA
    #intersect bigger than zero
    if(q > 0) {
      #hypergeometric test p-value
      pv = phyper(q,m,n,k,lower.tail=F)
    }
    corem.enrichment[x,] = c(q,m,n,k,pv)
  }
  #multiple hypotheses testing correction
  corem.enrichment = cbind(corem.enrichment,p_value.BH=p.adjust(corem.enrichment[,'p_value'],method='BH',n=nrow(corem.enrichment)))
  #select enriched corems with ten or more members
  final.enriched.corems = rownames(corem.enrichment)[which(corem.enrichment[,'p_value.BH']<=0.05 & corem.enrichment[,'m']> 9)]
  corem.enrichment[final.enriched.corems,]
}
#evaluate enrichment of EGRIN corems with differntially expressed genes of TetR baseline and response to tetracycline
modules.enriched.with.TetR.baseline<-evaluate.corem.enrichment(ecoli.corems, tetR.basal.degs)
modules.enriched.with.TetR.response<-evaluate.corem.enrichment(ecoli.corems, tetR.response.degs)
#save names of TF regulons over-represented in corems enriched with TetR basaline changes
tf.tf.associated.enriched.modules.basal<-c()
#save names of TF regulons over-represented in corems enriched with TetR response to tetracycline

#save genes in corems enriched with both TetR DEGs AND TF regulons

  temp<-evaluate.corem.enrichment(ecoli.corems, current.regulon)
  corem.intersect<-intersect(rownames(modules.enriched.with.TetR.baseline),rownames(temp))
  if(length(corem.intersect)>0)
  {
    tf.tf.associated.enriched.modules.basal<-c(tf.tf.associated.enriched.modules.basal,r)
    for(c in corem.intersect)
    {
      enriched.corems.tf.regulons.degs<-union(enriched.corems.tf.degs.genes,ecoli.corems[[c]])
      corem.count<-union(corem.count,c)
    }
      
  }
  #same analysis for TetR response to tetracycline
  corem.intersect<-intersect(rownames(modules.enriched.with.TetR.response),rownames(temp))
  if(length(corem.intersect)>0)
  {
    tf.tf.associated.enriched.modules.adaptive<-c(tf.tf.associated.enriched.modules.adaptive,r)
    for(c in corem.intersect)
    {
      enriched.corems.tf.regulons.degs<-union(enriched.corems.tf.regulons.degs,ecoli.corems[[c]])
      corem.count<-union(corem.count,c)
      
    }
  }
}

#Fig. 2B - plot selected TF regulons (for differentially active TFs)
handel.foldchange.matrix<-handel.average.expression[,2:4]-handel.average.expression[,1]
#Code to compute significance of fold-change of set of genes vs random selection
    permutation.function<-function(true.genes,column.of.fold.change.matrix)
    {
      N=100000
      true.average.fold.change<-mean(handel.foldchange.matrix[true.genes,column.of.fold.change.matrix])
      random.compilation<-c()
    for(n in 1:N)
    {
      random.fold.change<-handel.foldchange.matrix[sample(1:nrow(handel.foldchange.matrix),length(true.genes)),column.of.fold.change.matrix]
      random.compilation<-c(random.compilation,mean(random.fold.change))
    }
      pvalue<-length(which(abs(random.compilation) >= abs(true.average.fold.change)))/N
    pvalue
    }
par(mfrow=c(2,2))

selected.tfs<-c("arcA","marA","gadE")
#load prior network again
for(t in selected.tfs)
{
  tf.locus.tag<-strsplit(colnames(transcriptional.network)[grep(t,colnames(transcriptional.network))],split = "_")[[1]][2]
  if(t=="arcA")
  {
   #focus on ArcA repressed genes
  current.regulon.repression<-names(which(final.trn.network[,tf.locus.tag]<0))
    #focus on DEGs
    current.regulon.repression<-intersect(current.regulon.repression,tetR.DEGs)
    temporal.matrix<-rbind(cbind(handel.foldchange.matrix[current.regulon.repression,1],rep("WT(+)",length(current.regulon.repression))),
                           cbind(handel.foldchange.matrix[current.regulon.repression,2],rep("TetR(-)",length(current.regulon.repression))),
                           cbind(handel.foldchange.matrix[current.regulon.repression,3],rep("TetR(+)",length(current.regulon.repression))))
    temporal.matrix<-as.data.frame(temporal.matrix)
    colnames(temporal.matrix)<-c("Expression","Strain")
    temporal.matrix$Expression<-as.numeric(as.vector(temporal.matrix$Expression))
    temporal.matrix$Strain<-factor(temporal.matrix$Strain,levels = c("WT(+)","TetR(-)","TetR(+)"),ordered = TRUE)
    p <- ggplot(temporal.matrix, aes(x=Strain, y=Expression,fill=Strain)) + 
      geom_boxplot(position=position_dodge(0.8),color="red")+ theme(text = element_text(size=28))
    print(p+scale_fill_manual(values=rep("white",4)) + ggtitle(paste(t,"repression(",length(current.regulon.repression),")",sep="_")))
    print(permutation.function(current.regulon.repression,1))
    print(permutation.function(current.regulon.repression,2))
    print(permutation.function(current.regulon.repression,3))
  }
  
  else
  {
  current.regulon.activation<-names(which(final.trn.network[,tf.locus.tag]>0))
  if(length(current.regulon.activation)>0)
    {
   #Focus on DEGs
    current.regulon.activation<-intersect(current.regulon.activation,tetR.DEGs)
   temporal.matrix<-rbind(cbind(handel.foldchange.matrix[current.regulon.activation,1],rep("WT(+)",length(current.regulon.activation))),
                           cbind(handel.foldchange.matrix[current.regulon.activation,2],rep("TetR(-)",length(current.regulon.activation))),
                           cbind(handel.foldchange.matrix[current.regulon.activation,3],rep("TetR(+)",length(current.regulon.activation))))
  
    temporal.matrix<-as.data.frame(temporal.matrix)
    colnames(temporal.matrix)<-c("Expression","Strain")
    temporal.matrix$Expression<-as.numeric(as.vector(temporal.matrix$Expression))
    temporal.matrix$Strain<-factor(temporal.matrix$Strain,levels = c("WT(+)","TetR(-)","TetR(+)"),ordered = TRUE)
    p <- ggplot(temporal.matrix, aes(x=Strain, y=Expression,fill=Strain)) + 
      geom_boxplot(position=position_dodge(0.8),color="green")+ theme(text = element_text(size=28))
    print(p+scale_fill_manual(values=rep("white",4)) +  ggtitle(paste(t,"activation(",length(current.regulon.activation),")",sep="_"))) 
  }
    print(permutation.function(current.regulon.activation,1))
    print(permutation.function(current.regulon.activation,2))
    print(permutation.function(current.regulon.activation,3))
  }
}

#evaluating overlap between DEGs in TetR response and arcA KO in anaerobic growth (Covert et al. 2004; GEO accesion GSE1107)
arcA.ko.covert<-read.csv("../Data/Miscellaneous_files/arcA_ko_Covert2004.csv",header=T,row.names = 1)
#select replicates for WT and arcA KO in anaerobic conditions
arcA.ko.covert<-arcA.ko.covert[,c("ana_wt1","ana_wt2","ana_wt3","ana_wt4","ana_arcA1","ana_arcA2","ana_arcA3")]
#read microarray probes map
  arcA.microarray.probes.map<-read.csv("../Data/Miscellaneous_files/arcA_covert2004_probes_gene_map.csv")
arcA.microarray.probes.map<-arcA.microarray.probes.map[arcA.microarray.probes.map$ORF %in% rownames(handel.normalized.matrix),]
final.arcA.ko<-c()
genes.included.in.covert.data<-c()
for(g in 1:nrow(arcA.microarray.probes.map))
{
  current.gene<-as.character(arcA.microarray.probes.map$ORF[g])
  genes.included.in.covert.data<-c(genes.included.in.covert.data,current.gene)
  current.gene.pos<-grep(current.gene,rownames(arcA.ko.covert))
  final.arcA.ko<-rbind(final.arcA.ko,arcA.ko.covert[current.gene.pos,])
}
rownames(final.arcA.ko)<-genes.included.in.covert.data
#log2 transform the microarray data
final.arcA.ko<-log2(final.arcA.ko)
#perform differential expression analysis
arcA.response.covert<-bayesT(final.arcA.ko,numC = 4,numE = 3,conf = 7,doMulttest = T)
arcA.covert.log2FC<-arcA.response.covert$meanE - arcA.response.covert$meanC
names(arcA.covert.log2FC)<-rownames(arcA.response.covert)
arcA.degs.covert<-rownames(arcA.response.covert)[which(arcA.response.covert$BH < 0.05 & abs(arcA.response.covert$meanC - arcA.response.covert$meanE)>1)]
#genes differentially expressed in both Covert's data and TetR response to tetracycline
overlapping.DEGs<-intersect(arcA.degs.covert,tetR.response.degs)
#overlap significance 
phyper(99-1,248,4156-248,887,lower.tail = F)

}

3.3 Fig. 3B - microdilution growth curves

#miscellaneous function to convert time into the format required by Growthcurver
convert.time<-function(time.vector)
{
  new.out<-c()
  for(x in time.vector)
  {
    temporal.vector<-strsplit(x,split = ":")[[1]]
    new.out<-c(new.out, as.numeric(temporal.vector[1]) + ((as.numeric(temporal.vector[3]) + 
                                                  (60*as.numeric(temporal.vector[2])))/3600))
  }
  new.out<-round(new.out,digits = 3)
  new.out
}
#read OD data from Bioscreen experiment
growth.data<-read.csv("../Data/Fitness_BioscreenC/experiment2_formatted_data.csv",row.names=1)
time.data<-convert.time(rownames(growth.data))
rownames(growth.data)<-round(time.data,digits = 2)
blank.controls<-read.csv("../Data/Fitness_BioscreenC/blanks_data_formatted.csv",row.names=1)
time.data<-convert.time(rownames(blank.controls))
rownames(blank.controls)<-round(time.data,digits = 2)
blank.controls.average<-rowMeans(blank.controls)
growth.data<- growth.data - blank.controls.average
tetracycline.concentrations<-c(0, 4, 12, 16, 20) # ug/ml
strains<-c("WT","WTarcA","TetR","TetRarcA","pRB3.arcA")
number.replicates<-4
strain.colors<-c("#66C2A5","#FC8D62","#8DA0CB","#E78AC3","#A6D854")
#create Fig. 3B
#create data frame
temporal.df<-c()
#for 0 ug/ml and first four strains
    for(s in 1:4)
    {
      for(r in 1:number.replicates)
      {
      current.replicate<-paste(strains[s],0,"_",r,sep="")
      temporal.df<-rbind(temporal.df,cbind(rownames(growth.data)[1:49],growth.data[1:49,current.replicate],rep(strains[s],49)))
      }
    }
colnames(temporal.df)<-c("Time","OD","Replicate")
rownames(temporal.df)<-c()
temporal.df<-as.data.frame(temporal.df)
temporal.df$Replicate <- as.factor(temporal.df$Replicate)
temporal.df$Time<- as.numeric(as.vector(temporal.df$Time))
temporal.df$OD<- as.numeric(as.vector(temporal.df$OD))
#Function to estimate the average and standard deviation of each strain at each time point
compute.mean.and.sd<-function(input.df)
{
  time.values<-unique(input.df$Time)
  output<-c()
  for(t in time.values)
  {
    for(s in unique(input.df$Replicate))
    {
      temporal.mean<-mean(input.df$OD[which(input.df$Replicate==s & input.df$Time==t)])
      temporal.sd<-sd(input.df$OD[which(input.df$Replicate==s & input.df$Time==t)])
      output<-rbind(output,cbind(t,s,temporal.mean,temporal.sd))
    }
  }
  colnames(output)<-c("Time","Replicate","OD","sd")
  output<-as.data.frame(output)
  output$Time<-as.numeric(as.vector(output$Time))
  output$OD<-as.numeric(as.vector(output$OD))
  output$sd<-as.numeric(as.vector(output$sd))
  output
}
temporal.df2 <- compute.mean.and.sd(temporal.df)
temporal.plot<- ggplot(temporal.df2, aes(x=Time,y=OD, group=Replicate,colour=Replicate)) + 
  geom_line() +
  geom_point()+
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=OD-sd, ymax=OD+sd), width=0.75)
print(temporal.plot + scale_color_manual(values=strain.colors[c(3,4,1,2)])+
        theme(axis.text=element_text(size=30)) + xlab("Time(h)")+ylab("OD600"),main="[TET]=0")

#create panel for 20ug/ml of tetracycline (for TetR, TetR arcA and TetR arcA + pRB3-arcA)

for(s in 3:5)
    {
      for(r in 1:number.replicates)
      {
      current.replicate<-paste(strains[s],20,"_",r,sep="")
      temporal.df20<-rbind(temporal.df20,cbind(rownames(growth.data)[1:73],growth.data[1:73,current.replicate],rep(strains[s],73)))
      }
    }
colnames(temporal.df20)<-c("Time","OD","Replicate")

growthcurver.output.summary<-matrix(nrow=length(all.strains.tetracycline.combos),ncol=4,dimnames = list(all.strains.tetracycline.combos,c("max_r","t_mid","K","AUC")))

  growthcurver.output.summary[s,"t_mid"]<-round(mean(growthcurver.output.0.to.4ugml[grep(paste(s,"_",sep=""),growthcurver.output.0.to.4ugml$sample),"t_mid"]),digits = 2)

  growthcurver.output.summary[s,"AUC"]<-round(mean(growthcurver.output.0.to.4ugml[grep(paste(s,"_",sep=""),growthcurver.output.0.to.4ugml$sample),"auc_e"]),digits = 2)

4.2 Fig. 4B

#BioTek run for 24h, measurements every 30 mins
#sertraline concentrations (0,15,20,25,30,45,60,120 ug/ml)
#ten replicates per strain/concentration
sertraline.dose.response.growth<-read.csv("../Data/Sertraline_dilution/sertraline_dose_response_formatted_data.csv",header=T,row.names=1)
time.data<-convert.time(rownames(sertraline.dose.response.growth))
rownames(sertraline.dose.response.growth)<-round(time.data,digits = 2)
blank.controls.mean<-rowMeans(sertraline.dose.response.growth[,paste(rep(LETTERS[1:16],each=4),c(1,2,23,24),sep = "")])
sertraline.dose.response.growth<- sertraline.dose.response.growth - blank.controls.mean
#create matrix to save the number of replicates (out of 10) that passed the OD threshold for each concentration
sertraline.concentration<-c(0,15,20,25,30,45,60,120) # ug/ml
sertraline.matrix<-matrix(nrow=8,ncol=4,0,dimnames=list(sertraline.concentration,c("WT", "WTarcA","TetR", "TetRarcA")))
od.threshold<-0.1
for(i in 1:length(sertraline.concentration))
{
  #each row has only one sertraline concentration (see plate map file)
  #count how many WT replicates grew
  wt.row<-LETTERS[i]
  temporal.count<-0
  for(j in 3:12)
  {
    current.well<-paste(wt.row,j,sep="")
    #check change in OD after 24 hours of growth
    delta.od<-sertraline.dose.response.growth[49,current.well]-sertraline.dose.response.growth[1,current.well]
    if(delta.od>= od.threshold)
    {
      temporal.count<-temporal.count + 1
    }
  }
  sertraline.matrix[i,1]<-temporal.count
  #now for WT arcA
  temporal.count<-0
  for(j in 13:22)
  {
    current.well<-paste(wt.row,j,sep="")
    #check change in OD after 24 hours of growth
    delta.od<-sertraline.dose.response.growth[49,current.well]-sertraline.dose.response.growth[1,current.well]
    if(delta.od>= od.threshold)
    {
      temporal.count<-temporal.count + 1
    }
  }
  sertraline.matrix[i,2]<-temporal.count
  #now repeat the same analysis for TetR 
  tetR.row<-LETTERS[i+8]
  temporal.count<-0
  for(j in 3:12)
  {
    current.well<-paste(tetR.row,j,sep="")
    #check change in OD after 24 hours of growth
    delta.od<-sertraline.dose.response.growth[49,current.well]-sertraline.dose.response.growth[1,current.well]
    if(delta.od>= od.threshold)
    {
      temporal.count<-temporal.count + 1
    }
  }
  sertraline.matrix[i,3]<-temporal.count
  #now for TetR arcA 
  temporal.count<-0
  for(j in 13:22)
  {
    current.well<-paste(tetR.row,j,sep="")
    #check change in OD after 24 hours of growth
    delta.od<-sertraline.dose.response.growth[49,current.well]-sertraline.dose.response.growth[1,current.well]
    if(delta.od>= od.threshold)
    {
      temporal.count<-temporal.count + 1
    }
  }
  sertraline.matrix[i,4]<-temporal.count
}
#create heatmap
#heatmap breaks
my.breaks<-c(0,5,10)
pheatmap(sertraline.matrix[8:1,],scale="none",color= c("#BEAED4","#7FC97F"),
